data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['ɔmlit]
 Cách viết khác:
 omelet
◘['ɔmlit]
 ■như omelet

Anh - Anh
omelette
(US also omelet)
■ noun a dish of beaten eggs cooked in a frying pan and usually served with a savoury topping or filling.
Origin
Fr., earlier amelette (alt. of alumette), var. of alumelle, from lemele 'knife blade'.
